            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>B2 grammar points with HSK</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><b>"<a href="B2" class="mw-redirect" title="B2">B2</a>" (Upper Intermediate)</b> is the fourth level of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR). This pages shows the exact HSK Level equivalent of each B2 grammar point (instead of "Examples") for easy comparison between the two systems.
</p><p>There are <b>154</b> total grammar points in the list below.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="B2_grammar_points_with_HSK#Parts_of_Speech"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Parts of Speech</span></a>
